trend_summary: Across the time series the township stays largely low-rise, but vacant lots slowly filled with housing and small commercial blocks, and the highway interchange was widened. Central blocks became more continuous while tree cover along rivers and parks slightly increased. Overall medium-density, green suburban character remains.
notable_changes: Progressive infill housing on scattered vacant parcels, especially in central-west sectors.
Construction of several retail/office buildings with parking lots near the main northeast junction.
Widening and re-alignment of the eastern highway interchange, adding new ramps and lanes.
Expansion of an educational or institutional campus in the southwest, with new buildings and courts.
Denser riparian vegetation and park landscaping along the river corridor.
